Insert into CONTENIDO_AGENDA_I (ID_CONTENIDO,ID_IDIOMA,TITULO,CONTENIDO,SUBTITULO,LUGAR) values ('119','0','First General Conference of the European Coalition of Cities against Racism. ','<p>This Conference, entitled &laquo; Sharing Competence and Empowering Communities : The Role of Cities in Challenging Racism and Discrimination &raquo;, will take place from 10 to 12 May 2007 in Nuremberg, Germany. It will gather the member cities of the European Coalition, other municipalities and diverse actors of civil society committed against this challenging issue of racism and discrimination. First General Conference of the European Coalition of Cities against RacismThe 2007 European Year of Equal Opportunities for All was launched on 30 January 2007 in Berlin on the occasion of the first European Equality Summit. The European Coalition was presented at this meeting as a network of more than 60 municipalities coming from 14 countries of Europe engaged in the struggle against racism and discrimination. Closer cooperation with European Union (EU) institutions will be explored throughout the year 2007.</p><p>In this context and on the occasion of the German Presidency of the EU, the City of Nuremberg and UNESCO will co-organize the first General Conference of the European Coalition of Cities against Racism (ECCAR) from 10 to 12 May 2007 in Nuremberg. The Administrative Secretariat of the network has been located in this city since its creation in 2004.</p><p>The representatives of NGOs, target groups of discriminations and policy makers working at the municipal and European levels will be gathered around a panel discussion on &laquo; Overcoming Racism and Discrimination - Recommendations to Municipal Authorities &raquo;.</p><p>A series of thematic discussions are foreseen as well:</p><p>* &laquo; Racism and Discrimination in Europe: The Main Challenges Arising for Municipalities and How to Deal with Them &raquo;;</p><p>* &laquo; How to Promote the Cooperation of Municipalities at a National and at a European Level ? &raquo;;</p><p>* &laquo; How to Cooperate with Agents of Civil Society &raquo;;</p><p>* and &laquo; Implementation of Practical Examples in Education, Labour Market, Housing and Health &raquo;.</p><p>Young Europeans will also be mobilised to join the &laquo; Youth Forum &raquo;.</p><p>The Conference will also discuss a few ideas for collective actions proposed to the member cities in order to strengthen the network&rsquo;s capacity in terms of communication and research. After the adoption of the draft statute, the new Steering Committee will be elected.</p><p>For more information, please contact: Ms Jun Morohashi, <a href="mailto:j.morohashi@unesco.org">j.morohashi@unesco.org</a></p>',null,'Nuremberg (Germany)');
Insert into CONTENIDO_AGENDA_I (ID_CONTENIDO,ID_IDIOMA,TITULO,CONTENIDO,SUBTITULO,LUGAR) values ('120','0','Mediations of Cultural Difference: Debating Media and Diversity. European Workshop. ','<p>The necessity to have an ongoing debate on the &rsquo;political imaginary of heterogeneity&rsquo; (Werbner, 2002: 276) is revealed in the face-to-face encounters in the streets of today&rsquo;s metropoles, the mediated urban, national and transnational encounters within and beyond European cultural scapes, as well as in the mediated political actions and reactions around diversity and its implications. It is this articulation of the debate around cultural difference, communication, and the media that is the prime focus of this workshop. How might we view the media role in this discussion? And what about other forms of communicative practices that may feed into the debate? Who participates in the debate and what form does this participation take? Do the (new) media lead in new forms of identities, subjectivities and solidarities? Conversely, do they lead to new forms of exclusion and conformism, and to new fundamentalisms?<br /><br />In this spirit we call for papers that both participate in, and reflect upon the wider conduct of this debate. We invite submissions that engage with, but are not restricted to, the following themes:</p><p>* Cosmopolitanism, transnationalism and diasporas: thinking about the edges of the nation-state.</p><p>* Diaspora and cultural domesticity: sustaining traditions? The conservative aspects of cultural diversity</p><p>* Diasporas and alternative media: producing political &rsquo;meaning&rsquo;/ethics?</p><p>* The city and the urban politics of representation</p><p>* Cultural diversity and marginalized voices: politics of media representation and ethics</p><p>* Multicultural backlash: opposition to multiculturalism and the role of the media</p><p>* Bottom-up multiculturalism: everyday (multi)cultural encounters</p><p>* New media and multiculturalism: what does the internet add?</p><p>* Diaspora and digital narratives: loss, gain, negotiations, and interpretations</p><p>* Blogosphere and diasporas: a new public sphere?</p><p>* Media consumption: what can we learn from ethnic and diasporic media use?</p><p>* New theoretical interrogations on media, multiculturalism, cosmopolitanism, diaspora.<br /></p>',null,'University of Leeds. Leeds (Uk)');
Insert into CONTENIDO_AGENDA_I (ID_CONTENIDO,ID_IDIOMA,TITULO,CONTENIDO,SUBTITULO,LUGAR) values ('121','0','Seminario,  Educacin para la ciudadana.','<p>&Eacute;ste se enmarca dentro del proyecto de Ciudadanet, de educaci&oacute;n para el desarrollo. Con el seminario se persigue reunir a profesores, profesionales de la educaci&oacute;n, personas de diferentes asociaciones, y en general a todo el que est&eacute; interesado en la Particpaci&oacute;n Ciudadana.<br />Dirigido al profesorado y profesionales de la comunidad educativa, organizaciones y profesionales interesados en esta materia as&iacute; como ONGs, asociaciones de vecinos, entidades sin &aacute;nimo de lucro, organizaciones juveniles y voluntariado formal y no formal</p><p>Materias a tratar:<br />&nbsp;Ciudadan&iacute;a, migraciones y multiculturalidad; la participaci&oacute;n ciudadana en los centros educativos; voluntariado corporativo y fomento del asociacionismo; participaci&oacute;n ciudadana y ciudadan&iacute;a intercultural.</p><p>Inscripci&oacute;n gratuita</p><p>Confirmar asistencia en: Bad&iacute; Alias. Tel. 917014704</p><p><a href="mailto:educa3@fundeso.org">educa3@fundeso.org</a></p>','Los prximos 20 y 21 de abril tendr lugar el Seminario de Educacin para la Ciudadana en Madrid','Centro Hispano Africano. Madrid');
Insert into CONTENIDO_AGENDA_I (ID_CONTENIDO,ID_IDIOMA,TITULO,CONTENIDO,SUBTITULO,LUGAR) values ('122','0','Multiculturalismo, coeducacin y ciudadana. Conferencia de Alicia Miyares','<p>Este a&ntilde;o se presenta el libro Interculturalidad, feminismo y educaci&oacute;n, por una de sus autoras, Alicia Miyares, cuya conferencia se titula, &quot;Multiculturalismo, coeducaci&oacute;n y ciudadan&iacute;a&quot;.<br />La conferencia se celebra, en el sal&oacute;n de actos del Servicio Provincial de la Mujer, en c/ Carreter&iacute;a 60, 1&ordf; planta, a las 18,00 h., el lunes 23 de abril de 2007.<br />El acto se realiza en colaboraci&oacute;n con el Centro del Profesorado de M&aacute;laga, CEDMA y Centro C&iacute;vico de la Diputaci&oacute;n de M&aacute;laga.<br /><br />Alicia Miyares, es doctora en Filosof&iacute;a. Actualmente trabaja como consejera t&eacute;cnica de la Unidad de Mujeres y Ciencia del Ministerio de Educaci&oacute;n. Es secretaria de la &quot;Asociaci&oacute;n espa&ntilde;ola de filosof&iacute;a Mar&iacute;a Zambrano&quot;, integrante del Consejo rector del Instituto Asturiano de la Mujer. Es tambi&eacute;n, investigadora por Espa&ntilde;a en el proyecto europeo &quot;Europa para las mujeres&quot;. Sus l&iacute;neas de investigaci&oacute;n son los aspectos sociales, pol&iacute;ticos y morales del siglo XIX y su repercusi&oacute;n en la historia del feminismo, el feminismo como filosof&iacute;a pol&iacute;tica y la democracia actual y su perfeccionamiento. Ha impartido diversos cursos y seminarios en torno al feminismo y la filosof&iacute;a pol&iacute;tica y publicado, entre otros, los siguientes art&iacute;culos: introducci&oacute;n a La Biblia de la mujer (C&aacute;tedra,1997), El manifiesto de Seneca Falls (Leviatan,1999), La d&eacute;cada del &rsquo;t&uacute; mismo&quot; (Leviatan,1995), Los buenos sentimientos (Deva,1994) y El sufragismo (1994). Es autora del libro Nietzsche o la edad de la comparaci&oacute;n (Trabe, 2002) y Democracia Feminista, (C&aacute;tedra 2.003).<br /></p>','Como todos los aos, la Biblioteca del Servicio Provincial de la Mujer, organiza con ocasin del 23 de abril, da del libro, una conferencia en torno a un tema cuyo anlisis se realice desde la perspectiva de gnero.','Mlaga');
Insert into CONTENIDO_AGENDA_I (ID_CONTENIDO,ID_IDIOMA,TITULO,CONTENIDO,SUBTITULO,LUGAR) values ('123','0','II Festival Intercultural de Contes de Torrent (Valncia)','Com veureu la interculturalitat &eacute;s una de les caracter&iacute;stiques del Festival i volem invitar a contadors i contadores que vinguen d&rsquo;altres latituds a m&eacute;s dels contadors d&rsquo;altres pa&iuml;sos que ja viuen entre nosaltres. Entreu AC&Iacute; i descobriu els contadors que ens acompanyaran els dies del Festival. S&oacute;n molts, s&oacute;n especials, v&eacute;nen d&rsquo;ac&iacute; i de tot arreu... El continent afric&agrave; ha esta enguany l&rsquo;invitat especial amb Talik&eacute;, contacontes cantant de l&rsquo;illa de Madagascar amb el grup Tiharea, i a Leonard Logmo, director del Festival de Contes FESTMOC de Camer&uacute;n.<br />','Ja tenim enllestida la II Edici del Festival de contes de Torrent i enguany tenim moltes sorpreses. ','Valencia');
